# Navigation

| Command | Description | Example |
|----------|-------------|---------|
| `pwd` | Print the current working directory | `pwd` |
| `cd <dir>` | Change directory | `cd Documents` |
| `cd ..` | Go to the parent directory | `cd ..` |
| `cd ~` | Go to the home directory | `cd ~` |
| `cd` | Same as `cd ~` | `cd` |
| `cd /path` | Navigate using an absolute path | `cd /home/hamad` |

---

# Listing Files

| Command | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `ls` | List directory contents |
| `ls -a` | Show hidden files |
| `ls -l` | Long listing format |
| `ls -la` | Long listing + hidden files |

---

# File & Directory Creation

| Command | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `mkdir folder` | Create a directory |
| `mkdir dir1 dir2` | Create multiple directories |
| `touch file.txt` | Create an empty file |
| `tree` | Display the directory tree |

---

# File & Directory Removal

| Command | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `rm file.txt` | Remove a file |
| `rmdir folder` | Remove an empty directory |
| `rm -r folder` | Remove a directory recursively |
| `rm -rf folder` | Force remove recursively (**Dangerous**) |

---

# Path Symbols

| Symbol | Meaning |
|--------|---------|
| `/` | Root directory |
| `~` | Home directory |
| `.` | Current directory |
| `..` | Parent directory |

---

# Path Types

## Absolute Path

Starts from the root directory.

Example

```bash
/home/hamad/linux-practice/projects
```

---

## Relative Path

Starts from the current directory.

Example

```bash
projects/project1
```

---

# Hidden Files

Hidden files start with a dot (`.`).

Examples

```text
.bashrc
.profile
.config
.ssh
```

Show hidden files:

```bash
ls -a
```

---

# Permission Symbols

| Symbol | Meaning |
|--------|---------|
| `r` | Read |
| `w` | Write |
| `x` | Execute |
| `d` | Directory |
| `-` | Regular file |

Permission layout:

```text
Owner | Group | Others

rwx | r-x | r-x
```

